<div id="review_555412987" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/555412987" />
    <a title="Mscout" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1779306-mscout"><img alt="Mscout" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1286423193p2/1779306.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/555412987?book_show_action=true">Mar 07, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mscout" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mscout" href="/user/show/1779306-mscout">Mscout</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audio CD 9780061456428" href="/book/show/1976716.God_s_Problem">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1779306-mscout?shelf=history">history</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1779306-mscout?shelf=philosophy">philosophy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1779306-mscout?shelf=audio">audio</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1779306-mscout?shelf=religion">religion</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer555412987" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1841723183668550153">Ugh. Just an eight hour rant about how unfair it all is. Life is full of suffering and if He really wanted to, God could stop it. Ehrman gives a blow-by-blow of all the times God did or did not step in to stop the suffering of the Jews in the Bible. Additionally, he gives a rundown of all the suffering in the world today, from wars to genocide to natural disasters. And for the love of all that&apos;s holy, DON&apos;T get him started on childhood malaria...really not much more than an extended argument for</span>
  <span id="freeText1841723183668550153" style="display:none">Ugh. Just an eight hour rant about how unfair it all is. Life is full of suffering and if He really wanted to, God could stop it. Ehrman gives a blow-by-blow of all the times God did or did not step in to stop the suffering of the Jews in the Bible. Additionally, he gives a rundown of all the suffering in the world today, from wars to genocide to natural disasters. And for the love of all that's holy, DON'T get him started on childhood malaria...really not much more than an extended argument for his midlife conversion to agnosticism. </span>
  <a data-text-id="1841723183668550153" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


