<div id="review_1208645865" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1208645865" />
    <a title="John" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4842860-john"><img alt="John" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1446046075p2/4842860.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1208645865?book_show_action=true">Feb 22, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="John" class="user" itemprop="url" name="John" href="/user/show/4842860-john">John</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1208645865" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4120904393477287823">A bit windy and unnecessarily verbose, mostly by way of redundancy. But overall good. Great finishing line, &quot;just because we don&apos;t have the answer to suffering doesn&apos;t mean that we cannot have a response to it.&quot; Go ye and do likewise. </span>
  <span id="freeText4120904393477287823" style="display:none">A bit windy and unnecessarily verbose, mostly by way of redundancy. But overall good. Great finishing line, "just because we don't have the answer to suffering doesn't mean that we cannot have a response to it." Go ye and do likewise. </span>
